00:32:18,583 --> 00:32:19,709
Ba'el.

453
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:22,125
♪<i> Ylja'Qo</i> ♪

454
00:32:22,166 --> 00:32:26,125
♪<i> Ylja'Qo... ♪</i>

455
00:32:27,750 --> 00:32:30,000
♪<i> Van'aj javDich...</i> ♪

456
00:32:33,959 --> 00:32:36,333
Well, Worf, you've had quite
an effect on the young people.

457
00:32:36,375 --> 00:32:39,834
I have done nothing more
than show them who they are.

458
00:32:39,875 --> 00:32:44,667
No, you have shown them
what you want them to be.

459
00:32:47,917 --> 00:32:50,375
Tell me this.

460
00:32:50,417 --> 00:32:54,458
Do you know of any place,
any time in history

461
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:58,166
when Klingons and Romulans
have lived together in peace?

462
00:33:01,208 --> 00:33:03,458
We have despised each other,

463
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:06,875
fought each other
for centuries,

464
00:33:06,917 --> 00:33:09,250
except here.

465
00:33:09,291 --> 00:33:12,417
On this remote planet,

466
00:33:12,458 --> 00:33:17,083
Romulans and Klingons
live together in harmony.

467
00:33:20,750 --> 00:33:22,959
No government...

468
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:26,959
no leader has ever done
what I have done here.

469
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:29,041
And what about Toq?

470
00:33:29,083 --> 00:33:31,166
I saw what
happened to him

471
00:33:31,208 --> 00:33:34,417
when he caught the scent
of his prey on the wind.

472
00:33:34,458 --> 00:33:36,917
For the first time in his
life, he felt powerful,

473
00:33:36,959 --> 00:33:39,917
and<i> that</i> is what he has
been denied living here.

474
00:33:39,959 --> 00:33:43,542
And<i> that</i> is what you have
tried to take away from him.

475
00:33:43,583 --> 00:33:45,375
Now, you may be
content to sit here

476
00:33:45,417 --> 00:33:47,333
in the jungle
and wither to old age,

477
00:33:47,375 --> 00:33:49,208
but Toq and the others

478
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:51,959
have tasted what it is
to feel truly alive

479
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:54,166
and they will not
give that up now.

480
00:33:54,208 --> 00:33:56,000
Enough of this.

481
00:33:56,041 --> 00:33:59,709
We could talk all night
and<i> not</i> convince each other.

482
00:34:02,208 --> 00:34:05,083
I offer you a choice--

483
00:34:05,125 --> 00:34:08,583
live with us
as one of us...

484
00:34:10,125 --> 00:34:12,709
Or...?
Or I will have you...

485
00:34:15,208 --> 00:34:17,709
put to death.

486
00:34:17,750 --> 00:34:20,250
Then that is what
you will have to do.

487
00:34:20,291 --> 00:34:24,834
Worf, consider
this carefully.

488
00:34:24,875 --> 00:34:28,458
That death
will be honorable.

489
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:31,792
The young people will see
what it is to die...

490
00:34:31,834 --> 00:34:33,750
as a Klingon.

491
00:34:52,792 --> 00:34:55,542
(<i> knocking at door</i> )

492
00:34:55,583 --> 00:34:57,208
Enter.

493
00:34:58,917 --> 00:35:00,917
Thank you.

494
00:35:03,125 --> 00:35:05,000
I will remove
the tracking device.

495
00:35:05,041 --> 00:35:07,291
Then you can go over the wall
and hide in the jungle.

496
00:35:07,333 --> 00:35:10,041
Why are you doing this?

497
00:35:10,083 --> 00:35:12,083
My father is wrong.

498
00:35:12,125 --> 00:35:15,333
No matter how I might feel about
you, you don't deserve to die.

499
00:35:18,291 --> 00:35:20,750
I am not going
to run away, Ba'el.

500
00:35:20,792 --> 00:35:22,375
They will kill you.

501
00:35:22,417 --> 00:35:25,500
Yes, but they
will not defeat me.

502
00:35:25,542 --> 00:35:28,250
I don't understand you.

503
00:35:28,291 --> 00:35:31,625
A Klingon does not run
away from his battles.

504
00:35:31,667 --> 00:35:34,208
Is that really the lesson
you want us to learn?

505
00:35:34,250 --> 00:35:36,083
You've taught us
a great deal,

506
00:35:36,125 --> 00:35:38,750
awakened something inside us
that we never knew existed,

507
00:35:38,792 --> 00:35:41,959
but I don't understand what
we can learn from your death.

508
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:45,792
Then you do not yet understand
what it is to be Klingon.

509
00:35:46,959 --> 00:35:49,875
Worf...

510
00:35:49,917 --> 00:35:52,959
in spite of everything
that's happened,

511
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,000
I still sense that...

512
00:35:55,041 --> 00:35:57,667
that you care for me.

513
00:35:57,709 --> 00:35:59,750
Am I wrong?

514
00:36:01,542 --> 00:36:04,834
You talk so much
about being a warrior,

515
00:36:04,875 --> 00:36:07,834
about honor and death.

516
00:36:07,875 --> 00:36:11,041
Is it so hard
to speak of love?

517
00:36:11,083 --> 00:36:13,041
Worf, please.

518
00:36:18,667 --> 00:36:21,750
I would not have
thought it possible

519
00:36:21,792 --> 00:36:24,000
to love a Romulan.

520
00:36:24,041 --> 00:36:25,709
But you do.

521
00:36:28,417 --> 00:36:30,125
Yes.

522
00:36:30,166 --> 00:36:32,667
Well, if you've
come that far,

523
00:36:32,709 --> 00:36:34,542
can't you take it
one more step?

524
00:36:34,583 --> 00:36:38,291
Can't you stay here with us?
With me?

525
00:36:38,333 --> 00:36:41,834
If there<i> were</i> a way,

526
00:36:41,875 --> 00:36:44,083
I would take you
away with<i> me.</i>

527
00:36:47,333 --> 00:36:50,583
If there is anything
that I've learned from you--

528
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:53,125
from your reaction
to me--

529
00:36:53,166 --> 00:36:56,417
it's that I have
no place out there.

530
00:36:56,458 --> 00:36:58,875
Other Klingons
will not accept me

531
00:36:58,917 --> 00:37:00,417
for what I am.

532
00:37:00,458 --> 00:37:02,208
And if I stay here,

533
00:37:02,250 --> 00:37:05,250
<i>these</i> Klingons will not
accept me for what<i> I</i> am.

534
00:37:05,291 --> 00:37:07,208
Why did you come here?

535
00:37:07,250 --> 00:37:09,083
We were so happy.

536
00:37:09,125 --> 00:37:11,917
We didn't know that there was
anything missing in our lives.

537
00:37:11,959 --> 00:37:14,000
Ba'el...

538
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:28,500
Good-bye, Worf.

539
00:37:32,917 --> 00:37:35,333
(<i> door closes</i> )

540
00:37:38,959 --> 00:37:41,125
(<i> murmur of conversation</i> )

541
00:38:06,333 --> 00:38:09,250
I know that there
are those among you

542
00:38:09,291 --> 00:38:12,667
who may question
what I am about to do,

543
00:38:12,709 --> 00:38:16,375
and you would not
be wrong to do so.

544
00:38:16,417 --> 00:38:18,125
I have questioned myself.

545
00:38:18,166 --> 00:38:20,792
I have spent the night
considering my decision--

546
00:38:20,834 --> 00:38:24,917
challenging myself to
justify whether it<i> is</i> right

547
00:38:24,959 --> 00:38:27,125
and I have reached
the conclusion

548
00:38:27,166 --> 00:38:30,083
that it is
absolutely necessary...

549
00:38:30,125 --> 00:38:32,834
to put this man to death.

550
00:38:32,875 --> 00:38:35,834
What we have
built together

551
00:38:35,875 --> 00:38:38,166
would be destroyed
by this man

552
00:38:38,208 --> 00:38:41,291
and I cannot allow
that to happen.

553
00:38:45,125 --> 00:38:49,166
I give you one last chance
to accept our way of life.

554
00:38:49,208 --> 00:38:52,792
Those are eloquent words,
Tokath,

555
00:38:52,834 --> 00:38:56,667
but the truth is,
I am being executed

556
00:38:56,709 --> 00:38:59,458
because I brought
something dangerous

557
00:38:59,500 --> 00:39:03,083
to your young people--
knowledge.

558
00:39:03,125 --> 00:39:06,417
Knowledge of their origins,

559
00:39:06,458 --> 00:39:09,500
knowledge of the real reasons
you are here in this camp.

560
00:39:09,542 --> 00:39:11,542
The truth is
a threat to you.

561
00:39:11,583 --> 00:39:13,458
Enough.

562
00:39:14,417 --> 00:39:15,959
Stand ready.

563
00:39:20,333 --> 00:39:22,417
Raise your weapons.

564
00:39:24,542 --> 00:39:26,875
Father...
TOQ: Stop this!

565
00:39:35,125 --> 00:39:36,875
If you kill him,

566
00:39:36,917 --> 00:39:39,333
you will have to kill<i> me.</i>

567
00:39:46,125 --> 00:39:48,083
Step aside, Toq.

568
00:39:48,125 --> 00:39:51,291
Worf would rather die
than accept this way of life

569
00:39:51,333 --> 00:39:53,792
and so would I.

570
00:39:53,834 --> 00:39:57,458
I want to leave,
as do many others.

571
00:39:57,500 --> 00:40:01,500
You will have to kill us
to keep us here.

572
00:40:03,125 --> 00:40:06,041
You see, Tokath...

573
00:40:06,083 --> 00:40:08,625
it is already
too late.

574
00:40:08,667 --> 00:40:11,125
I'm warning you.

575
00:40:11,166 --> 00:40:13,834
Move aside now.

576
00:40:14,834 --> 00:40:17,125
Stand ready.

577
00:40:18,458 --> 00:40:21,291
Toq... move away.

578
00:40:23,041 --> 00:40:24,458
Take aim...

579
00:41:04,083 --> 00:41:06,000
Ba'el.

580
00:41:06,041 --> 00:41:07,709
Tokath.

581
00:41:13,417 --> 00:41:15,625
Long ago,

582
00:41:15,667 --> 00:41:19,166
when your captives
asked to stay here,

583
00:41:19,208 --> 00:41:21,709
our hope was to avoid

584
00:41:21,750 --> 00:41:25,125
dishonoring our children
on the homeworld,

585
00:41:25,166 --> 00:41:27,125
but perhaps
over the years,

586
00:41:27,166 --> 00:41:30,500
we lost sight of
our children

587
00:41:30,542 --> 00:41:32,083
that we raised here.

588
00:41:32,125 --> 00:41:34,542
This is<i> our</i> prison.

589
00:41:34,583 --> 00:41:35,834
(<i> sighs</i> )

590
00:41:35,875 --> 00:41:38,125
It should not
be theirs.

591
00:42:01,291 --> 00:42:05,250
Years ago, your parents
made a great sacrifice

592
00:42:05,291 --> 00:42:07,041
for the sake
of their families.

593
00:42:07,083 --> 00:42:10,333
Today,
they do so again.

594
00:42:10,375 --> 00:42:12,709
For that,
we must honor them.

595
00:42:14,625 --> 00:42:16,667
You<i> must</i> promise them

596
00:42:16,709 --> 00:42:19,542
never to reveal
their secret.

597
00:42:21,375 --> 00:42:24,625
No one must know
of this place.

598
00:42:27,583 --> 00:42:30,625
A supply ship is due
in a few days.

599
00:42:30,667 --> 00:42:32,458
They will take us.

600
00:42:32,500 --> 00:42:36,375
When they arrive,
Tokath will explain it to them.

601
00:42:36,417 --> 00:42:39,208
Then we will start
a new life.

602
00:42:45,208 --> 00:42:47,375
<i>Captain's Log,</i>
<i>supplemental:</i>

603
00:42:47,417 --> 00:42:49,333
<i>Our search for Lieutenant Worf</i>
<i>was cut short</i>

604
00:42:49,375 --> 00:42:51,500
<i>when we received</i>
<i>a cryptic message from him</i>

605
00:42:51,542 --> 00:42:53,834
<i>requesting a rendezvous</i>
<i>with a Romulan vessel.</i>

606
00:42:53,875 --> 00:42:57,458
<i>He has informed us we will</i>
<i>be taking on passengers.</i>

607
00:43:03,125 --> 00:43:05,500
It's good to see you.

608
00:43:08,542 --> 00:43:10,333
He seems fine.

609
00:43:10,375 --> 00:43:13,875
We're giving everyone
a thorough checkup in Sick Bay.

610
00:43:18,125 --> 00:43:19,792
Thank you, Doctor.

611
00:43:19,834 --> 00:43:23,625
Welcome home,
Mr. Worf.
Thank you, sir.

612
00:43:23,667 --> 00:43:25,667
Picard to Bridge.

613
00:43:25,709 --> 00:43:29,083
Signal the Romulan ship that
the last group is on board.
BRIDGE: Aye, sir.

614
00:43:29,125 --> 00:43:32,875
You found what you were
looking for, Mr. Worf?

615
00:43:34,417 --> 00:43:37,750
No, sir.
There was no prison camp.

616
00:43:37,792 --> 00:43:40,041
Those young people are
survivors of a vessel

617
00:43:40,083 --> 00:43:42,709
that crashed in the Carraya
system four years ago.

618
00:43:44,333 --> 00:43:46,625
No one survived Khitomer.

619
00:43:48,542 --> 00:43:51,125
I understand.
